{
  "doc_id": "38971",
  "text": "Among surgical treatments for osteoporotic vertebral fractures, percutaneous surgical procedures including vertebroplasty and kyphoplasty are commonly performed [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Several complications may develop during the earlyand late-term postoperative period [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . New fractures are among these complications. Various risk factors have been identified to be associated with occurrence of new fractures in the postoperative period [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] . However, it is unclear whether or not mobilization time (hours) is a risk factor.",
